title: Grateful Dead Live at Boston Tea Party on 1969-12-30
lineage: SBD > MC > C > D > CD > EAC > SHN
description: Good Lovin'-> Drums-> Good Lovin', Mama Tried, New Speedway Boogie, Casey Jones, Black Peter, Me & My Uncle, Midnight Hour, Cumberland Blues, Cryptical Envelopement-> Drums-> The Other One-> Cryptical Envelopement-> Cosmic Charlie Uncle John's Band-> Mason's Children-> China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Dark Star-> Alligator-> Drums-> The Eleven-> Alligator-> We Bid You Good Night

reviews.review_text: Closing Out the Decade Hard to believe this show has not been reviewed (maybe it hasn't been up that long??).  Anyway this is a very long, very solid show, and pretty good quality.  Long winding jams form the last half of the show, but there are some bad cuts.
Holy Moly...listen to the melodic harmonies of New Speedway Boogie Wow.....

Strange I think Dark Star( from what I gather) was an invitation.
Either teamed with cryptical(good) or alligator(bad) but it was the neutral.

best of run I like this show better than the following night, personally. Good Lovin' is really shaping up into something special, New Speedway is very nice, other than botched lyrics, the Black Peter is certainly the best of the year (gets *intense*), Mason is hot, Dark Star is AMAZING (steel yourself for the cut at the end though).  Great the way Alligator unexpectedly morphs into the Eleven, then returns for an abbreviated version of Alligator -> Caution -> Feedback.  Would be five stars is the quality was this high all night.

Whoa Wow.  Did anyone hear the jam that morphed from the  eleven at about 10:15? Fantastic...then a sweet AWBYG to take us into a quick Alligator.  The jamming on the 11->AWBYG makes the show for me.

sounds quality is a little rough though...tweek the eq for best results.
